title: Home | United States Interagency Council on Homelessness
description: USICH is the only federal agency with the sole mission of preventing and ending homelessness in America. We coordinate with our 19 federal member agencies, state and local governments, and the private sector to create partnerships, implement evidence-based best practices, and use resources in the most efficient and effective ways.
